## Resolved Decisions

> [!NOTE]
> **Priority tier: P2.5c — Pipeline Security Hardening.** Positioned between P2.5b (completed wiring) and P2.6 (Service Daemon). Security hardening runs immediately after pipeline wiring is done. **Decision: adopted.**

> [!NOTE]
> **MEU numbering: MEU-PH{N} prefix.** Continues the `MEU-PW{N}` convention from P2.5b. Range: `MEU-PH1` through `MEU-PH10`. **Decision: adopted.**

> [!NOTE]
> **Gap G: New MEU (MEU-PH7).** Assertion gates get a new MEU rather than reopening MEU-86 (`transform-step`, ✅ approved). MEU-PH7 touches the same `transform_step.py` file but tracks as independent work. **Decision: new MEU.**

---

## Proposed Changes

### New Build Plan Documents

#### [NEW] [09c-pipeline-security-hardening.md](file:///p:/zorivest/docs/build-plan/09c-pipeline-security-hardening.md)

**Scope:** Gaps A, B, B+ (safety foundations)

Contains:
- §9C.1 — StepContext deep-copy boundary + `Secret` carrier class (`safe_copy.py`)
- §9C.2 — SQL sandbox module (`sql_sandbox.py`): `set_authorizer`, `mode=ro`, `PRAGMA query_only=ON`, `trusted_schema=OFF`, `progress_handler`, sqlglot AST allowlist
- §9C.3 — SendStep confirmation gate (`requires_confirmation` field)
- §9C.4 — FetchStep content-type validation + fan-out cap
- §9C.5 — Secrets scanning (regex guard on policy save/emulation)
- §9C.6 — Content-addressable policy IDs (`sha256(canonical_json)`)

**Dependencies:** None (foundational layer)

---

#### [NEW] [09d-pipeline-step-extensions.md](file:///p:/zorivest/docs/build-plan/09d-pipeline-step-extensions.md)

**Scope:** Gaps C, D, F, G (new step types + language extensions + schema v2 migration)

Contains:
- §9D.1 — QueryStep (`query_step.py`): read-only SQL via sandbox, parameterized binds, row limit, fan-out cap, ref support
- §9D.2 — ComposeStep (`compose_step.py`): multi-source data merging, merge strategies, section assembly
- §9D.3 — Variable injection: `PolicyDocument.variables` dict + `RefResolver` `{var: ...}` pattern
- §9D.4 — Assertion gates: `TransformStep` `kind=assertion` discriminator, `ConditionEvaluator` arithmetic extensions
- §9D.5 — Step-count cap (20 steps max via Pydantic validator)
- §9D.6 — Schema version v1→v2 migration: dual-schema `model_validator`, v1/v2 gating, backward-compatible opt-in

**Dependencies:** §9C.2 (SQL sandbox) must exist before QueryStep

---

#### [NEW] [09e-template-database.md](file:///p:/zorivest/docs/build-plan/09e-template-database.md)

**Scope:** Gap E (template database entity + hardened rendering)

Contains:
- §9E.0 — Boundary input contract: write surfaces, schema owners (`EmailTemplateCreateRequest`/`EmailTemplateUpdateRequest`), `extra="forbid"`, error mapping, create/update parity
- §9E.1 — `EmailTemplateModel` SQLAlchemy model (11 columns)
- §9E.2 — `EmailTemplateRepository` (CRUD + name-lookup)
- §9E.3 — `HardenedSandbox` (`ImmutableSandboxedEnvironment` + filter allowlist + attribute deny-list)
- §9E.4 — `safe_markdown.py` (`nh3` + `markdown-it-py` render chain)
- §9E.5 — Updated `SendStep._resolve_body()` resolution chain (5 tiers)
- §9E.6 — Template size caps (64 KiB source, 256 KiB output)
- §9E.7 — Alembic migration for `email_templates` table

**Dependencies:** None (independent of SQL sandbox)

---

#### [NEW] [09f-policy-emulator.md](file:///p:/zorivest/docs/build-plan/09f-policy-emulator.md)

**Scope:** Gap H (policy emulator with security controls)

Contains:
- §9F.1 — `PolicyEmulator` class: 4-phase dry-run (PARSE → VALIDATE → SIMULATE → RENDER)
- §9F.2 — Output containment controls (4 KiB per-call cap, cumulative 64 KiB session budget)
- §9F.3 — SHA-256 hashed RENDER output (agent gets hash, not raw content)
- §9F.4 — `EmulatorError` + `EmulatorResult` Pydantic models (structured error schema)
- §9F.5 — Anonymized snapshot DB for SIMULATE phase
- §9F.6 — `source_type` output metadata field (`db | provider | computed`)

**Dependencies:** All of 09c, 09d, 09e (emulator validates all step types + templates)

---

#### [MODIFY] [05g-mcp-scheduling.md](file:///p:/zorivest/docs/build-plan/05g-mcp-scheduling.md)

**Scope:** Gap I (11 new MCP tools + 4 new MCP resources + boundary-input contract)

**New tools:**
- `emulate_policy` — core emulator endpoint with output containment
- `list_step_types` — registered step type discovery
- `list_db_tables` — schema discovery for QueryStep SQL authoring
- `get_db_row_samples` — sample rows for template `sample_data_json`
- `validate_sql` — pre-flight SQL validation against AST allowlist
- `list_provider_capabilities` — provider discovery with `docs_url`
- `create_email_template` — template CRUD
- `get_email_template` — template read
- `list_email_templates` — template listing
- `update_email_template` — template update
- `preview_email_template` — template rendering via `HardenedSandbox`

**New resources:**
- `pipeline://templates` — available DB templates with names and required variables
- `pipeline://db-schema` — queryable table/column schema for query step SQL authoring
- `pipeline://emulator/mock-data` — sample mock data sets for each data_type
- `pipeline://providers` — provider names, data types, auth methods, docs_url

**Boundary-input contract:** Zod `.strict()` schemas for all write surfaces (`create_email_template`, `update_email_template`, `emulate_policy`, `validate_sql`). Invalid input → MCP `INVALID_PARAMS` error, not downstream 500. Create/update parity enforced via shared `HardenedSandbox` compile check. Cross-ref: [09e §9E.0](file:///p:/zorivest/docs/build-plan/09e-template-database.md) for Python-side contract.

**Dependencies:** 09e (template DB), 09f (emulator), 09c (SQL sandbox)

