### Dependency Graph (MEU Execution Order)

```mermaid
graph TD
    PH1["MEU-PH1: stepcontext-safety<br/>(Gap A)"] --> PH8
    PH2["MEU-PH2: sql-sandbox<br/>(Gap B)"] --> PH4
    PH3["MEU-PH3: send-fetch-guards<br/>(Gap B+)"] --> PH8
    PH4["MEU-PH4: query-step<br/>(Gap C)"] --> PH5
    PH4 --> PH8
    PH5["MEU-PH5: compose-step<br/>(Gap D)"] --> PH8
    PH6["MEU-PH6: template-database<br/>(Gap E)"] --> PH8
    PH6 --> PH9
    PH7["MEU-PH7: policy-vars-assertions<br/>(Gaps F+G)"] --> PH8
    PH8["MEU-PH8: policy-emulator<br/>(Gap H)"] --> PH9
    PH9["MEU-PH9: emulator-mcp-tools<br/>(Gap I)"] --> PH10
    PH10["MEU-PH10: default-template"]

    style PH1 fill:#ff6b6b,stroke:#c92a2a,color:#fff
    style PH2 fill:#ff6b6b,stroke:#c92a2a,color:#fff
    style PH3 fill:#ff6b6b,stroke:#c92a2a,color:#fff
    style PH4 fill:#ffa94d,stroke:#e8590c,color:#fff
    style PH5 fill:#ffa94d,stroke:#e8590c,color:#fff
    style PH6 fill:#69db7c,stroke:#2b8a3e,color:#fff
    style PH7 fill:#69db7c,stroke:#2b8a3e,color:#fff
    style PH8 fill:#4dabf7,stroke:#1971c2,color:#fff
    style PH9 fill:#b197fc,stroke:#7048e8,color:#fff
    style PH10 fill:#b197fc,stroke:#7048e8,color:#fff
```

**Parallelization opportunities:**
- MEU-PH1 + PH2 + PH6 can run in parallel (no mutual deps)
- MEU-PH3 depends on PH2 (uses sandbox connection patterns)
- MEU-PH4 + PH5 + PH7 can run in parallel after PH2 completes
- MEU-PH8 waits for all of PH1–PH7
- MEU-PH9 waits for PH6 + PH8
- MEU-PH10 is a trivial final task

